oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Petition to the Lewis County Court
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A petition to members of the Lewis County court by J.P. Dabbs, MD, regarding Tennessee's Public Health Bill and county health boards. Dabbs wants to amend the standing healthcare system by abolishing the salary system.
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Dabbs, J. P.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: New Deal 1933-1939; New Deal, 1933-1939--Tennessee
